Reviewed `findProjectRootDir`; I found **2 issues** in the current implementation.

| Severity | Finding | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| **medium** | The new fallback is **hard-coded to `pulsar-common`**, so `findProjectRootDir(startDir)` is no longer actually searching for a project root generically. If the tree under `startDir` contains a valid Browser4 root but no `pulsar-common`, or contains some other `pulsar-common` first, the method returns `null` or the wrong root even though a `VERSION`-rooted project exists. | `pulsar-core\pulsar-common\src\main\kotlin\ai\platon\pulsar\common\code\ProjectUtils.kt:53-57` |
| **medium** | The deep-search fallback introduces an **unbounded recursive walk of the whole working tree** on startup. `LocalResourceProperties.load()` now calls `findProjectRootDir()` while loading config, and the fallback uses `startDir.walk().firstOrNull(...)` with no pruning for `.git`, `target`, `build`, etc. If the process starts from a large workspace parent instead of inside the repo, config loading can degrade into a full-tree scan. | `pulsar-core\pulsar-common\src\main\kotlin\ai\platon\pulsar\common\code\ProjectUtils.kt:53-57`, `pulsar-core\pulsar-common\src\main\kotlin\ai\platon\pulsar\common\config\LocalResourceProperties.kt:60-64` |

